BRIEFING: WIDESPREAD HEAVY SHOWERS AND STRONG THUNDERSTORMS ASSOCIATED WITH A COLD FRONT WILL CONTINUE TO IMPACT THE EASTERN END OF THE STATE. HEAVY SHOWERS AND ISOLATED THUNDERSTORMS WILL SHIFT EAST OVER BIG ISLAND THIS MORNING. THERE WILL STILL BE INTENSE RAINFALL RATES WITHIN THE STRONGEST CELLS THAT ARE CAPABLE OF PRODUCING LOCALIZED FLASH FLOODING. STRONG WESTERLIES ARE ALSO STILL POSSIBLE AS THIS AREA OF RAIN AND THE TRAILING COLD FRONT PASSES ACROSS BIG ISLAND THROUGH THE DAY.
SENTRY ALOHA JAN 29 - FEB 12 MIL 1/31 - 11 SORTIES @ 1830Z, 8 @ 2330Z
